  <!-- LOCAL KNOWLEDGE -->
  <section class="local-section" id="local">
    <h2>Chimney Sweeping in Point Cook</h2>
    <div class="local-box"><p>Point Cook is one of Melbourne's largest growth suburbs, a planned residential development on the Werribee plain south of the Princes Freeway that has expanded from a small population in the early 1990s to one of the largest residential areas in metropolitan Melbourne. The suburb's housing stock is almost entirely estate housing from the 1990s through to the present — large four and five bedroom homes on generous lots in a series of master-planned residential estates. A defining characteristic of the newer estate homes throughout Point Cook is the widespread installation of slow combustion wood heaters: in a suburb where ducted gas is expensive and the open Werribee plain creates genuinely cold winters, slow combustion heaters were specified in a large proportion of estate homes from the late 1990s onward and continue to be installed in new builds. Point Cook's coastal plain position directly on Port Phillip Bay's western shore means the suburb experiences cold winter winds off the bay and the Werribee plain simultaneously — south-westerly airflows can be sharp and persistent, making the wood heater a genuine winter necessity in many households. Many of these heaters are now reaching an age where they have been in regular use for a decade or more without a professional flue clean, and annual servicing is both a safety and a performance issue. We service Point Cook and the surrounding Wyndham suburbs regularly.</p></div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNS -->
  <section class="signs-section" id="signs">
    <h2>Signs Your Point Cook Chimney Needs Cleaning</h2>
    <ul class="signs-list">
      <li>Slow combustion heater smoking back into the room at the start of winter</li>
      <li>Poor heating performance — the heater runs but the room doesn't warm up properly</li>
      <li>A smoky or acrid smell when the heater is operating or after it is shut down</li>
      <li>Tar or creosote visible around the heater flue collar or ceiling plate</li>
      <li>A heater that has been in regular use for several winters without a professional service</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- SERVICES -->
  <section class="services-section" id="services">
    <h2>Chimney Services in Point Cook</h2>
    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card"><h3>Chimney Sweep</h3><p>Full brush sweep from firebox to pot. Soot, creosote and debris removed. Verbal condition report included.</p></div>
